FT  13 FEB 92 / International Company News: TRW unveils Dollars 140m deficit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TRW, the US automotive, space and information services group, yesterday
unveiled a loss of Dollars 140m for 1991 after taking a final quarter
restructuring charge of Dollars 256m, which the management had warned about
in December.
Excluding the charge, which was taken to help fund an overhaul of TRW's
businesses - including a 10,000 workforce reduction, big cuts in capital
spending, and up to Dollars 500m of asset sales - the group made a net
profit of Dollars 25m in the fourth quarter and Dollars 116m in the year,
both well down on earnings at the same stage of 1990.
The picture throughout TRW's divisions was the same: sales were higher in
the fourth quarter than a year ago, but full-year sales were flat or lower
than in 1990. Overall, group sales were up 3 per cent in the quarter at
Dollars 2.1bn, but down 3 per cent over the full year at Dollars 7.9bn.
The figures were well received on Wall Street yesterday, with TRW shares
rising Dollars 1 to Dollars 44 3/4 .
