<HEADLINE>
FT  13 FEB 92 / The Lex Column: Burton
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Burton may have an impressive line-up of non-executives these days, but its
boardroom problems are as intractable and expensive as ever. In looking to
Debenhams for yet another chief executive, the group is hoping to make
better use of talent within its only consistently successful retailing
chain. A profound shake-up of its other stores is an urgent requirement, but
that was equally the case a year or two ago. Until it finally happens,
Burton's shares will doubtless remain as unfashionable as some of its
clothes.
