<HEADLINE>
FT  13 FEB 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Australian Wool Corporation's market indicators, the most widely used
overall guide to the course of the wool market,on February 12 reached 597
cents a Kg., exactly back to the closing level reached at the end of last
season. Prices for some wools are well above that basis and others fall far
short of it, but there is no doubt that the wool market is now seen as
nearly certain to reach new peaks in the free market era. Demand is
particularly strong for middle range categories, where drought has
supplemented production cuts by farmers.
</TEXT>
