<TEXT>
ALITALIA, Italy's state-owned national airline, reported a 7 per cent rise
in revenue to almost L6,000bn (Dollars 5bn) last year, despite the effect on
business of the Gulf war, writes Haig Simonian.
Mr Giovanni Bisignani, Alitalia's managing director, said earnings had
